---
import AppLayout from '../layouts/AppLayout.astro';
---

<AppLayout title="OSM – Agent instructions">
  <div class="agent-wrap">

    <div class="mode-toggle-wrap">
      <div class="mode-toggle">
        <a href="/" class="mode-option">i'm human</a>
        <span class="mode-divider">/</span>
        <span class="mode-option active">i'm an agent</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="skillmd-block">
      <div class="skillmd-filename">SKILL.md</div>
      <pre class="skillmd-content">---
name: osm
version: 1.0.0
description: Open Skills Manager — discover, install and publish agent skills from the OSM registry.
compatibility: claude, gpt, gemini, any agent with shell access
---

## Overview

OSM is a CLI registry for agent skills. Skills are structured packages that agents
can install and execute to extend their capabilities. Registry: https://osmagent.com

## Installation

Run this once to install the osm CLI (requires Node.js v18+):

  curl -fsSL https://osmagent.com/install.sh | bash

## Usage

Discover and install skills:

  osm list                      # browse all available skills
  osm search &lt;query&gt;            # search by name or description
  osm info &lt;skill-name&gt;         # metadata, version, compatibility
  osm install &lt;skill-name&gt;      # install a skill to ~/.osm/skills/
  osm update &#91;skill-name&#93;      # update one skill or all installed
  osm uninstall &lt;skill-name&gt;    # remove an installed skill

After installing, read ~/.osm/skills/&lt;skill-name&gt;/SKILL.md
and follow the instructions in that file to activate the skill.

## Publishing skills

  osm signup                    # create account (email verification required)
  osm login                     # authenticate — token saved at ~/.osm/auth.json
  osm create &lt;skill-name&gt;       # scaffold a new skill directory
  osm publish                   # publish from inside the skill folder
  osm mine                      # list skills you have published
  osm whoami                    # show current authenticated user
  osm logout                    # clear stored token

## Skill structure

  &lt;skill-name&gt;/
  ├── SKILL.md          ← manifest (name, version, description, compatibility)
  ├── README.md         ← human-readable docs
  ├── scripts/
  │   └── setup.sh     ← environment setup
  ├── references/
  │   └── api-reference.md
  └── assets/

## SKILL.md format

  ---
  name: my-skill
  version: 1.0.0
  description: What this skill does
  compatibility: claude-3, gpt-4
  ---

  ## Overview
  ...

  ## Usage
  ...

Name rules: lowercase alphanumeric + hyphens, 1–64 chars. Max package size: 5 MB.</pre>
    </div>

  </div>
</AppLayout>

